content:
**What do I mean when I reference a stock that is digesting?**

Stocks donâ€™t go straight up in a vacuum... they move in staircase patterns: up, sideways, up, sideways.

Imagine the market just ate a massive buffet (say, 40% gains). It canâ€™t just keep shoving food in... it needs to digest. It needs to sit on the couch, do nothing for a bit, and eventually, it will process what it consumed and make room for the next meal.

Thatâ€™s what a stock is doing in digestion.
